



Head Quarters, Cambridge, Septr 21st 1775.



Parole Hanover.
Countersign, Ipswich


Whereas frequent Applications are making to the General, Commander in Chief, by Officers of all Ranks & Denominations, for an allowance of Rations of provisions, which are not only absolutely necessary, but usual and customarily allowed to themThe General has thought proper to order, and direct, that from the first day of July last, there be Issued by the Commissary General, the following proportion of rations. Vizt




Rations


To each
Major General
15.



Brigdr General
12.



Colonel
6.



Lt Colonel
5.



Major
4.



Captain
3.



Subaltern
2.


and to
each Staff Officer
2.


